TI  - Vegetation development on the Hirschkopf landslide - succession on raw calcareous and marly soils
T2  - FORSTWISSENSCHAFTLICHES CENTRALBLATT
LA  - German
AB  - In 1983 more than 50 ha woodland were devastated by a landslide. In 1985-1995 the vegetation development was studied. The newly formed raw soils are still covered by initial stages of vegetation development. The progress of succession depends on supply of diaspores, nature of the soils, and microclimatic conditions. On the raw calcareous soils Stipion calamagrostis communities established themselves, the raw marry soils were covered by communities of Petasition paradoxi and Dauco-Melilotion. Reforestation is starring very slowly and depends on the increasing humic content of the raw soils.
