FX  - The authors are sincerely grateful to the two anonymous reviewers and to the editors who significantly improved the manuscript. The research was funded within the following projects: (i) PRIN 2010-2011 project (grant number 2010AYKTAB_006) 'Response of morphoclimatic system dynamics to global changes and related geomorphological hazards', Ministero dell'Istruzione, dell'Universita e della Ricerca - MIUR; (ii) Fondi Potenziamento della Ricerca - Linea 2 -2015 Project 'Dynamic of active margins: from rift to collisional chains', leader Dr. Davide Zanoni, Ministero dell'Istruzione, dell'Universita e della Ricerca - MIUR, University degli Studi di Milano, Earth Science Department "A: Desio". The authors thank: (i) Prof. G. Forno and Prof. M. Gattiglio for the fruitful discussions on the site of Saint Nicolas; (ii) G. Volpi, Dr. E. Miascotti, and Dr. M. Pellegrini for the collaboration in the field and during the elaboration of the geopedological and dendrogeomorphological analysis in the laboratory; (iii) Daniele Cat Berro (SMI, Italian Society of Meteorology), Arpa Piemonte, and Arpa Valle d'Aosta for validating and providing meteorological records; (iv) Antonio Borello, Ente di Gestione dei Parchi delle Alpi Cozie for helpful assistance in the field and the sharing of information. The authors are also grateful to the local public administration that provided the permits to sample vegetation, to collect soil samples, and to use the private roads.
