KW  - MOVEMENT MECHANISM
KW  - KIIRUNAVAARA MINE
KW  - GROUND MOVEMENT
KW  - DEFORMATIONS
KW  - HANGINGWALL
KW  - PREDICTION
KW  - COLLAPSE
AB  - In order to obtain the subsidence mechanism of a mountain surface in the Daliang Lead-zinc Ore Mine in China, the engineering geological conditions in the mining area of the Daliang Lead-zinc Ore Mine were analyzed in detail by combining the results of the site investigations and allowing the characteristics of the surface subsidence events to be summarized. Field investigation and numerical simulation were used to reveal the subsidence mechanism of the mountain surface caused by underground ore body mining. The results showed that there are four groups of dominant structural planes of the dolomite, dolomite (broken), and sandstone. The dominant structural planes of the ore body are three groups. The open pit slope had successively experienced the following processes: stability, slope collapse, large area collapse, surface collapse cave, surface collapse landslide, and northern slope collapse. The formation mechanism of a later collapse pit can be divided into four stages: the deformation stage of overlying strata, the landslide stage of the mountain surface, the caving and collapse stage of the mountain surface, and the collapses of the mountain surface. The formation process of the landslide was reproduced by numerical simulation. The displacement of the west slope landslide area in the vertical and horizontal directions showed that the mountain is in the landslide stage, which is consistent with the actual situation of the mine. The reliability of the numerical model was verified. There are three abrupt change points in the development process of vertical displacement. The development of vertical displacement can be divided into four stages. The research results provide a reference for mine safety production and collapse pit treatment.
